The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at Rice University in Houston, Texas, expressing renewed American efforts to bring economic pressure on the regime in Venezuela. Pence stated that Nicolás Maduro is a dictator with no legitimate claim to power and must go. He also highlighted the United States' recognition of Interim President Juan Guaidó as the only legitimate leader of Venezuela. Pence listened to stories from individuals impacted by the crisis in Venezuela and expressed solidarity with them. He emphasized the commitment of the United States to stand with the Venezuelan people until Maduro is removed from power and freedom is restored.